WHO   — The Dead-Man's Switch — the monitoring pattern where a cron must check in on each run, and silence raises an alarm — the practice that catches the 3am job that quietly stopped running
WHAT  — the monitoring pattern where a cron must check in on each run, and silence raises an alarm — the practice that catches the 3am job that quietly stopped running
WHERE — CRN · The Cron Job — Unix scheduling, ~1975 → today (LOGISMÓS domain)  Framework inputs: cron; crontab; crond; the schedule; the box; the watch  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — It is accountability inverted: instead of trusting the job ran, you demand proof, so the unwitnessed becomes witnessed by its own absence.
HOW   — Crystallized from the history & practice of cron.

